  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/261013315?book_show_action=true">Jan 12, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kari" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kari" href="/user/show/101554-kari">Kari</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781612130910" href="/book/show/13003360-behind-closed-doors">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/101554-kari?shelf=ipad">ipad</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/101554-kari?shelf=2012">2012</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer261013315" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12264333996796826364">Behind Closed Doors is not only a great mystery, but it is a story about second chances and new love. Both Elizabeth and Christopher have been hurt in the past by their spouses. Yet, they are drawn to each other from the first. I loved them together and it was so fun watching them fall in love with each other. The epilogue was just so sweet! The peripheral characters, especially Christopher&apos;s family, round out the story nicely. I hope Ms. Hayes will feature more of the brothers in future books! </span>
  <span id="freeText12264333996796826364" style="display:none">Behind Closed Doors is not only a great mystery, but it is a story about second chances and new love. Both Elizabeth and Christopher have been hurt in the past by their spouses. Yet, they are drawn to each other from the first. I loved them together and it was so fun watching them fall in love with each other. The epilogue was just so sweet! The peripheral characters, especially Christopher's family, round out the story nicely. I hope Ms. Hayes will feature more of the brothers in future books! The mystery of who is trying to scare Elizabeth was well written. I was kept guessing until the end and I will admit that I was wrong about who it was..I love when that happens! I definitely recommend this book. It will suck you right in and you won't want to put it down until you finish it!</span>
  <a data-text-id="12264333996796826364" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

