<span id="freeTextContainer15575398821798040136">I have read three other books by this author, so I was not at all surprised how easily I was wrapped up in the story of &quot;Behind Closed Doors&quot;.<br/><br/>The story of Chris and Elizabeth is not at all the typical love story. I was drawn in from the start wondering about their separate pasts and how they had come to live one floor apart in Springfield, Ohio. The plot is well thought out and was a true page turner. The possible villain in this story numbered more than one and kept me guessing until the big re</span>
  <span id="freeText15575398821798040136" style="display:none">I have read three other books by this author, so I was not at all surprised how easily I was wrapped up in the story of "Behind Closed Doors".<br /><br />The story of Chris and Elizabeth is not at all the typical love story. I was drawn in from the start wondering about their separate pasts and how they had come to live one floor apart in Springfield, Ohio. The plot is well thought out and was a true page turner. The possible villain in this story numbered more than one and kept me guessing until the big reveal.<br /><br />Overall, Ms. Hayes does it again with this Romantic/Suspense. I can't wait to read the second novel in the Daniel's Brothers series, "Red Zone".</span>
